  <div class="block-3">
    <div class="inner-block" id="responsibilities">
      <section class="responsibilities_for_ministerial_role responsibilities" id="responsibilities_for_ministerial_role_1086">
        <h1>Responsibilities</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Her specific responsibilities include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Court services and reform (including Bills)</li>
  <li>Legal aid</li>
  <li>Legal support and fees</li>
  <li>Administrative justice and tribunals</li>
  <li>Criminal justice</li>
  <li>Family justice</li>
  <li>Supporting the Secretary of State on EU exit and international business</li>
  <li>Shadow Commons minister for Lord Keen portfolio (except for Civil Liabilities Bill)</li>
  <li>Parliamentary Minister (SIs)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
        <section class="current-role-holder" id="current-role-holder">
          <h1>Current role holder: <span class="name">Lucy Frazer QC MP</span>
</h1>
          <div class="govspeak">
<p>Lucy Frazer QC was appointed as Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Ministry of Justice on 9 January 2018.</p>

<p>She was elected as Conservative MP for South East Cambridgeshire in 2015.</p>
</div>
          <div class="read-more">
            <a href="/government/people/lucy-frazer">More about this person</a>
          </div>
        </section>



      
